***************************************************************************

Description:

	configurate vim plugin automaticlly

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Operation:
	
	1.configuration
		1.1.execute "auto_profile.sh"
	   *the text of "vimrc" add to "/etc/vim/vimrc"*
	   *copy "ct" command to "/usr/local/bin"* 

	2.use command
		2.1."ct --help" get help
		2.2."ct" create tags and cscope.out
		2.3."ct --create" create files.conf
		2.4."ct --remmove" clean all files created 

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Function:

	1.Ctags	
		"ctl+]" =>> jump function definition
		"ctl+t"	=>> comeback previous position

	2.Tlist
		"tl" =>> function list

	3.Cscope
		"\+g" =>> jump position of function definition
		"\+c" =>> jump position which the function called
		"\+s" =>> all position of the function 

	4.winManager
		"wm" =>> file list

	5.MiniBufExpl
		"bn" =>> next buff
		"bp" =>> previous buff

	6.Lookup
		"F5" =>> search files

	7.Grep
		"F3" =>> search string 

	8.c\h
		"F12" =>> jump include file

	9.Vsearch
		"*" =>> next position
		"#" =>> previous position
		*you must in visual modle*

***************************************************************************
